OL,7,F"He is now facing a prison sentence
OL,8,Ffor his actions and I hope this serves
OL,9,Fas a stark reminder that online
OL,10,Factions have consequences."
OL,12,FA second man in Wales has also been
OL,13,Fjailed for encouraging people on
OL,14,Fsocial media to start a riot.
OL,16,FRichard Williams, 34, posted about
OL,17,Ftaking part in a riot and shared a
OL,18,Fderogatory meme about migrants in a
OL,19,Flocal Facebook group dedicated to
OL,20,Fprotests, the Crown Prosecution
OL,21,FService (CPS) said.
